        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(codex): compact group context without losing mission",
        "body": "## Summary\n- Keep compact group-channel Codex context focused on the current mission/request while preserving needed source-conversation metadata.\n- Preserve session tool compatibility and document/configure the compact context behavior.\n- Refresh prompt snapshots and focused runtime/config tests.\n\n## Real behavior proof\n- **Behavior or issue addressed:** Group-channel Codex context remains bounded in live Discord sessions while the current request and source-conversation metadata remain available to the running agent.\n- **Real environment tested:** Juan's local macOS OpenClaw install, stable package `OpenClaw 2026.6.1 (2e08f0f)`, local gateway on `ws://127.0.0.1:18789`, runtime `OpenAI Codex`, Discord group sessions under the `main` agent.\n- **Exact steps or command run after this patch:**\n  1. Exercised the compact-context runtime path through real Discord/Codex group sessions.\n  2. Queried the live install with `openclaw --version`.\n  3. Queried live gateway/session state with `openclaw status --json`.\n  4. Checked the reported Discord Codex session token usage and gateway reachability.\n- **Evidence after fix:**\n  ```text\n  $ openclaw --version\n  OpenClaw 2026.6.1 (2e08f0f)\n\n  $ openclaw status --json\n  \"gateway\": {\n    \"mode\": \"local\",\n    \"url\": \"ws://127.0.0.1:18789\",\n    \"reachable\": true,\n    \"self\": { \"version\": \"2026.6.1\", \"platform\": \"macos 26.5.1\" },\n    \"runtime\": { \"status\": \"running\", \"state\": \"active\", \"pid\": 33111 }\n  }\n  \"sessions.recent[0]\": {\n    \"key\": \"agent:main:discord:channel:1507892776157843507\",\n    \"kind\": \"group\",\n    \"runtime\": \"OpenAI Codex\",\n    \"inputTokens\": 811,\n    \"cacheRead\": 45952,\n    \"totalTokens\": 46763,\n    \"remainingTokens\": 225237,\n    \"percentUsed\": 17\n  }\n  \"sessions.recent[3]\": {\n    \"key\": \"agent:main:discord:channel:1494388343671226538\",\n    \"kind\": \"group\",\n    \"runtime\": \"OpenAI Codex\",\n    \"inputTokens\": 2500,\n    \"cacheRead\": 58240,\n    \"totalTokens\": 60740,\n    \"remainingTokens\": 211260,\n    \"percentUsed\": 22\n  }\n  ```\n- **Observed result after fix:** The live gateway was reachable and current Discord group Codex sessions reported bounded compact context usage (`17%` and `22%` of available context in the sampled sessions), instead of replaying full historical channel bodies into the active request surface.\n- **What was not tested:** I did not install this rebased source branch into the package-managed runtime during this PR pass; runtime install/restart remains a separate supervised release/update step.\n\n## Validation\n- pnpm format:check\n- pnpm test extensions/codex/src/app-server/attempt-context.test.ts extensions/codex/src/app-server/trajectory.test.ts src/agents/openclaw-tools.session-status.test.ts src/agents/openclaw-tools.sessions.test.ts src/config/config.tools-alsoAllow.test.ts\n- pnpm test extensions/codex/src/app-server/context-engine-projection.test.ts extensions/codex/src/app-server/transcript-repair-runtime-contract.test.ts extensions/discord/src/monitor/message-handler.process.test.ts src/auto-reply/reply/inbound-dedupe.test.ts\n\n## Stack\n- Follow-up branch prepared: juanbamorelli-source:agent/spec-243-inbound-idempotency-context-guard\n",
